# Copy to .env.local (gitignored). Vite only exposes vars prefixed VITE_ to
# client code — and "exposes" is literal here: unlike the Android app (where a
# key is merely extractable from an APK with some effort), every one of these
# keys is plainly visible in this app's network tab and bundled JS the moment
# anyone opens devtools. There is no backend to hide them behind.
#
# For a personal/small-group deployment this is a fine tradeoff. If this ever
# gets real traffic, the right fix is routing ORS/NLR/OCM/Overpass calls
# through a thin serverless proxy (a Vercel/Cloudflare function) that holds
# the real keys server-side and rate-limits by IP — not something to build
# preemptively before it's needed, but flagging now so it's a deliberate
# choice later, not a surprise.

VITE_ORS_API_KEY=
VITE_NLR_API_KEY=
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
